com.github.jhanne82.documenttree

Class DocumentTree<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.jhanne82.documenttree.DocumentTree<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the elements of terms describing the document.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NumberDocumentTree

    public abstract class DocumentTree<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    Generic abstract class which implements a binary tree to store Document This implementation provides methods to
  • fill the tree by a given list of Documents
  • Breadth First Search
  • Depth First Search
  • Random Walker Search
  • reposition of documents

      • level_order_insert

        public void level_order_insert(DocumentNode<T> root,
                               Document<T>[] documents,
                               int start,
                               int size)
        Recursive method to create a tree from an array of Documents. The tree will be placed under a given node. If root is null a root node will be generated.
        Parameters:
        root - defines the node under which the tree should be placed.
        documents - defines the array of documents which should be inserted.
        start - defines the index from which the insert should start from the given array.
        size - defines the number of the documents which should be added to the tree. Size should be less or equal than the size of the document array.

      • breadthFirstSearch

        public DocumentList<T> breadthFirstSearch(int maxVisitedNode,
                                          T[] searchTerm,
                                          int searchTimeStamp)
        Method which will perform a search using Breadth First. Breadth-first search (BFS) is an algorithm for traversing or searching tree or graph data structures. It starts at the tree root and explores the neighbor nodes first, before moving to the next level neighbours. The search will be performed until maxVisitedNodes are searched.
        Parameters:
        maxVisitedNode - defines how many nodes will be searched
        searchTerm - defines the term vector of the search request
        searchTimeStamp - defines the given timestamp of the search which will be stored on the search document
        Returns:
        a list of documents sorted by relevance
        See Also:
        DocumentList

      • depthFirstSearch

        public DocumentList<T> depthFirstSearch(int maxVisitedNode,
                                        T[] searchTerm,
                                        int searchTimeStamp)
        Method which will perform a search using Depth First. Depth-first search (DFS) is an algorithm for traversing or searching tree. One starts at the root and explores as far as possible along each branch before backtracking. The search will be performed until maxVisitedNodes are searched.
        Parameters:
        maxVisitedNode - defines how many nodes will be searched
        searchTerm - defines the term vector of the search request
        searchTimeStamp - defines the given timestamp of the search which will be stored on the search document
        Returns:
        a list of documents sorted by relevance
        See Also:
        DocumentList

      • randomWalkSearch

        public DocumentList<T> randomWalkSearch(int maxVisitedNode,
                                        T[] searchTerm,
                                        int searchTimeStamp)
        Method which will perform a search by walk randomly through the tree. After a node was searched it will be randomly defined if the next node will be considered by breadth or depth first search. The search will be performed until maxVisitedNodes are searched.
        Parameters:
        maxVisitedNode - defines how many nodes will be searched
        searchTerm - defines the term vector of the search request
        searchTimeStamp - defines the given timestamp of the search which will be stored on the search document
        Returns:
        a list of documents sorted by relevance
        See Also:
        DocumentList

      • repositionOfDocuments

        public int repositionOfDocuments(int numberOfRelevenceCalculationToRepositiong,
                                 int timestampOfLastSearch,
                                 int threshold)
        Will do a reposition of the documents in the tree. As first step the document will be switched related to the average relevance of the last searches. As second step these documents can be switched which were not searched for a specified time (defined via threshold).
        Parameters:
        numberOfRelevenceCalculationToRepositiong - defines the number of required searches on a document to perform a document switch depending on the average relevance.
        timestampOfLastSearch - defines the timestamp of the last perfomed search on the tree
        threshold - defines the limit for searches which were NOT performed on the documents which allows them to switch them independent from the average relevance
        Returns:
        the number of documents which were switched
